# CyberFin Nexus — Implementation Walkthrough

Privacy-first platform fusing cyber threat telemetry with financial transactions using GNNs and Federated Learning to detect money mule rings.

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Data Generator] --> B[Graph Builder]
    B --> C[GAT Model]
    B --> D[FL Engine]
    C --> E[Adversarial Sim]
    C --> F[Audit Trail]
    C --> G[Streamlit Dashboard]
    D --> G
    E --> G
    F --> G
```

## Files Created

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [data_generator.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/data_generator.py) | Synthetic accounts, transactions, cyber events, mule rings |
| [graph_builder.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/graph_builder.py) | Heterogeneous PyG graph (account↔device↔transaction) |
| [gat_model.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/models/gat_model.py) | 3-layer GAT with multi-head attention + explainability |
| [fl_engine.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/federated/fl_engine.py) | FedAvg + Gaussian DP noise for cross-bank collaboration |
| [adversarial_sim.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/rl/adversarial_sim.py) | 4 attack strategies with adaptive retraining |
| [audit_trail.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/blockchain/audit_trail.py) | SHA-256 hash chain for tamper-evident audit |
| [config.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/utils/config.py) | Centralized configuration |
| [metrics.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/utils/metrics.py) | AUC, precision, recall, F1, ROI helpers |
| [app.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/app.py) | 1200-line Streamlit dashboard (6 tabs) |

## Key Metrics

| Metric | Value |
